The paper deals with the problem of detecting targets using an antenna array and recording reflected echoes, which is a common problem in remote sensing. The approach used in the paper is based on compressive sensing, which is a key concept in the field of information theory (cs.IT). The paper also involves signal processing (cs.SI) and computer vision (cs.CV) techniques for detecting targets and reconstructing the scene. The use of numerical simulations suggests that the paper may also be relevant to the field of numerical analysis (cs.NA) and multimedia (cs.MM).
